div.span: The Node.js container manages real-time communication through WebSockets, enabling instant updates between clients and the backend. It listens for events triggered by Laravel and broadcasts changes to connected users. Containerized with Docker, it ensures fast, scalable, and reliable real-time messaging.

It communicates with the Laravel API for core features and listens to Node.js for real-time updates. Built with cross-platform support, it runs natively on iOS and Android.

div.div: The IoT component is powered by the Atom Lite (ESP32), which captures sensor data and sends it to the Laravel backend via HTTP. It enables real-time monitoring of physical conditions like seat occupancy. Compact and Wi-Fi enabled, it bridges hardware inputs with the digital system seamlessly.

div.div: The React.js frontend serves as the web interface for admins and owners, providing real-time dashboards and management tools. It communicates with the Laravel API for data and listens to the Node.js WebSocket server for live updates. Built for responsiveness and speed, it runs in the browser and adapts to various devices.
